A Niger Delta Group under the aegis of Peace Development Security And Humanitarian Rights Association Of Niger Deltans has joined World Leaders and millions of well-wishers across the globe to celebrate and to congratulate the newly inaugurated President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, His Excellency, Senator Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria and the First Lady, Her Excellency, Senator Oluremi Tinubu for their well-deserved honour. Comrade Mike J K Tiemo, the President of the Group who spoke to newsmen in Warri Delta State conveyed their warmest greeting and wished the first family and Mr President in particular thevery best of time on the saddle as the number one citizen of our great nation, Nigeria. Comrade Mike Tiemo also expressed confidence that based on the pedigree of his antecedent in office as the former Governor of Lagos State , President Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu has the cognate wealth of experience, the wherewithal and the prerequisites needed to function optimally in the exalted office of Mr President to move Nigeria to greater heights. The Niger Delta Humanitarian Activist recalled that when Tinubu was Governor in Lagos State, he positively impacted the people across the board without discrimination and tribal inclinations, adding that he believe without any iota of doubt that , President Tinubu will do better because he has listening ears. The Group pointed out that there is a need to implore all aggrieved opposition party Leaders and members to consider God Almighty the creator of heaven and earth and also to reflect on the noble path of former President Goodluck Ebele Jonathan Who took a candid decision to concede to the outgoing President Muhammadu Buhari during the 2015 General Election He stressed that for peace and tranquility to prevail for the overall interest of all Nigerians , it is germanefor all hands to be on deck togive President Ahmed Bola Tunubu Asiwaju a chance because no body knows the mind of God. The Group President urged Nigeriansto pray for the unity, success and progress of the country in the era of Alhaji Asiwaju Ahmed Bola Tinubu on the saddle as Mr President. POLL In a related development, Comrade Mike JK Tiemo the Group President threw their Weight behind Senator Godswill Akpabio’s bid to emerge as Senate President in the 10th National Assembly. The Niger Delta Peace Group opined that Senator Godswill Akpabio’s performance index in the past is robust enough to merit him the office of the Senate President. The Group canvassed the view that of all the candidates on parade for the control of the red chambers as the number three citizen, Senator Godswill Akpabio stands ahead because he is tested and can be trusted to perform credibly well in the office of the Senate President for the overall growth and development of Nigeria in general.